the ears of his close friends. After two years of performing almost every other week, playing some of Denver's best venues, as well as going on tour with their friends in The Coast is Ours, White Flag Raised decided to call it a day. WFR played it's final show in August of 2013 at the famous Gothic Theatre in Englewood, CO.

Even after they disbanded, music was still a very important part of their lives. After a few months of talking and a lot of exciting new ideas, three of the former members decided to embark on a new journey and start a new project called "Tonight We Rise".

Tonight We Rise will be hitting the studio in May 2014 to start recording a full length album at Denver's own Rusty Sun Audio. Their musical journey is one which has required a lot of hard work and dedication. Tonight We Rise is working harder than ever before to release new music and start playing performances again.
